<TITLE> 10 Shibir activists arrested over meeting in Gopalganj </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Gopalganj, Nov 9 (bdnews24.com)  Police Thursday arrested Gopalganj district president, general secretary and eight more activists of Islami Chhatra Shibir, the student wing of Jamaat-e-Islami, on charges of breaching the emergency powers rules. Md Soiruddin Ahmed, Gopalganj Sadar Police Station chief, said acting on a tip-off, they raided the library of Rokonuddin Trust at Miaparha in Gopalganj town and arrested 10 Shibir activists while they were holding a clandestine meeting under the emergency rule. The arrestees are district Shibir president Md Moniruzzaman Khan Alamgir, 25, general secretary Md Solaiman Siddiqui Badal, 22, Md Rafiqul Islam, 25, Md Mokarram Billah, 22, Masum Billah, 21, Najmul Hossain, 19, Inamul Haque, 22, Syed Ikramul, 18, Md Mamun Khandakar, 17, and Md Sohrab Hossain Sheikh, 14 from Gopalganj, Faridpur and Narail districts, police said. Unwilling to be named, local people said despite the emergency rule, the Shibir activists would frequently assemble at the Trust and hold meetings clandestinely. Their movements and behaviour too were highly suspicious, they added. It was alleged that the Shibir activists gathered there defying the emergency to hold their monthly meeting. A case had been filed with Gopalganj Sadar Police Station and the exact purpose of their gathering there would be determined after investigation, police said. bdnews2
